HagensborgResources Ltd said it will receive a seven mln dlrs Canadianline of credit from the Bank of Novia Scotia to develop asalmon farming operation.    The company said the funds will be used to completeconstruction of the land-based operation at Nanaimo in BritishColumbia.    Details of the credit line are being finalized with theBank of Novia Scotia with the financing to be fully guaranteedby Norway-based Den Norske Creditbank and the NorwegianGuarantee Institute for Export Credit, it added. Reuter&#3;